# oracle/metric.md — tolerance-aware LLM-ON correctness for <PRODUCT>

> Ground-truth TYPE = **MIXED**. Each layer of the proposal is scored by its own
> type. This document is the authoritative definition `oracle/src/bin/oracle_score.rs`
> implements; the scorer is LLM-free and re-scores byte-identically.

## What the AI proposes, and what is scored

<PRODUCT>'s AI proposes <WHAT> from <INPUTS>; a deterministic kernel then
<computes/retrieves> the load-bearing value(s). The precision question is the
SPEC's: *<the product's stated precision metric>*.

## The three layers

| Layer | Type | What is scored | Tolerance | Authority |
|---|---|---|---|---|
| **Deterministic** | exact | the proposal carries inputs through unchanged + the product kernel's output is **bit-identical** to expected; the product verifier accepts | **exact** (`f64::to_bits`; product verifier tolerances) | `<product_kernel>` + `<product_shell>::verification::verify` |
| **Standard-derived** | set | every proposed value ∈ `<product>_oracle::reference::ALLOWED` (normalised) | **set-membership** | `reference` (cite <public clause(s)>) |
| **Judgmental** | banded | `|proposed_soft − reference_soft|` ≤ <BAND> | **diagnostic only, NOT gated** (reference `pending-founder`) | agent-seeded reference |

## Overall per-case PASS

```
PASS(case) := deterministic_ok(case) AND standard_ok(case)
precision_pct = 100 * (#PASS) / (#cases)
```

The judgmental band is recorded (`judgmental_in_band`) but NOT a PASS conjunct.

## What this does / does not claim

- **Does:** the AI never fabricates a load-bearing value + stays internally
  consistent (deterministic), and stays within the standard vocabulary (standard).
- **Does NOT:** assert the proposal is *certified accurate* or that the reference
  data is itself correct. <Tool-qualification / signed-reference items> remain
  founder items.
